  <!-- FAQs Widget ******************* -->

  <FAQs
    title="Frequently Asked Questions"
    subtitle=""
    highlight="FAQs"
    items={[
      [
        {
          question: 'Do you provide code to do XYZ?',
          answer:
            'We will work on code for any infrastructure supported by Public Cloud APIs.<br><br> For Applications, we are focused on containerized applications which includes modernizing legacy applications to run in containers and orchestrating the deployment and integration of those containers with any other services',
        },
        {
          question: "Can you help us with solution design?",
          answer:
            "Cloudsmart only provides 'Day 1' work, that is 'creating the infrastructure and application configuration'. 'Day 0' is the design phase which produces the product requirements that are the inputs Cloudsmart needs.<br><br> For Day 0 design work, we have a Partner Network that can assist",
        },
        {
          question: "Can you monitor and manage the solution",
          answer:
            "You will be please to know that this is called 'Day 2'. We don't currently plan to support Day 2 (maintainance, monitoring and optimizing) and, once again, we will refer you to our Partner Network."
        },
      ],
      [
        {
          question: 'What does "Unlimited" mean',
          answer:
            'Unlimited means you can add as many tasks as you like to your Product Backlog and a DevOps engineer will work through them, one at a time.',
        },
        {
          question: 'What if the engineer is slow?',
          answer:
            "For sure, some tasks can take longer and this is normal however, we should try to spot these tasks ahead of time and either break them down or re-priorise them. <br><br>We do this in a Planning Session ahead of starting work",
        },
        {
          question: 'I have paid for my Unlimited plan and would like a refund',
          answer:
            "If, for any reason you are not satisfied, we may issue a refund which would be pro-rated back from the time you cancel.<br><br> This would only apply if claimed prior to the delivery of work because, delivery ('handing over') implies your implicit acceptance per the Definition of Done created in initial Planning",
        },
      ],
    ]}
